What was changed
1. Created run_backend.py — PyInstaller entry point
Resolves .env from the exe's directory (not PyInstaller's temp _MEIPASS folder)
Sets cwd to the exe's directory so logs/ and .env are found
Starts uvicorn programmatically on port 8000
2. Updated main.py:13-21 — frozen-exe compatibility
Minimal change: added sys.frozen detection so BACKEND_DIR and .env loading use the exe's directory instead of _MEIPASS when running as an exe. Zero behavior change when running normally with Python.

3. Built run_backend.exe (~22 MB)
PyInstaller --onefile build with all FastAPI/uvicorn dependencies bundled.

4. Updated electron/main.cjs — spawn exe instead of Python
Replaced PYTHON_EXE + ["-m", "uvicorn", ...] with BACKEND_EXE (run_backend.exe)
Added pre-check: if exe doesn't exist, shows clear error dialog
All other behavior unchanged (polling, kill on quit, mic permissions, etc.)


Commands
Rebuild the exe (after backend code changes)
cd backend
.\.venv\Scripts\pyinstaller.exe --onefile --name run_backend ^
  --hidden-import=main ^
  --hidden-import=uvicorn.logging --hidden-import=uvicorn.loops ^
  --hidden-import=uvicorn.loops.auto --hidden-import=uvicorn.protocols ^
  --hidden-import=uvicorn.protocols.http --hidden-import=uvicorn.protocols.http.auto ^
  --hidden-import=uvicorn.protocols.websockets --hidden-import=uvicorn.protocols.websockets.auto ^
  --hidden-import=uvicorn.lifespan --hidden-import=uvicorn.lifespan.on ^
  --hidden-import=uvicorn.lifespan.off --hidden-import=truststore ^
  --hidden-import=httpx --hidden-import=dotenv ^
  --add-data "main.py;." run_backend.py

Test the exe manually
cd backend
dist\run_backend.exe
# Then open http://localhost:8000/docs in browser — you should see the FastAPI Swagger UI

Run the full desktop app
cd VMA-frontend
npm run desktop
This starts Vite (port 3000) → Electron launches → spawns run_backend.exe (port 8000) → polls until ready → opens window. When you close the app, the backend exe is killed automatically.


